wikipedia_page.main: Joseph Wells (30 December 1855 – 1929) was a British author and Oxford academic, where he served as Vice-Chancellor from 1923 to 1926.Educated at Reading School and the Queen's College, Oxford, Wells became a tutor in 1883 and then in 1913 Warden of Wadham College, Oxford.

link_mentions.page: List of vice-chancellors of the University of Oxford

response: * Joseph Wells (cricketer) (1828–1910), English cricketer, father of author H. G. Wells
* Joseph Wells (academic) (1855–1929), British author and Oxford academic
* Joseph Wells (politician) (1773–1853), British-born Upper Canada politician and soldier
